<h1>Network Access Control Changes</h1>
<ul>
<li>
<h2>Motivation: Many of the LSM network security fields and hooks
rejected for 2.5.</h2>
</li>
<li>
<h2>Retained general socket layer hooks and Unix domain socket
hooks.</h2>
</li>
<li>
<h2>Reworking sock_rcv_skb hook and NetFilter hooks to provide
subset of original SELinux functionality.</h2>
</li>
<li>
<h2>Revisiting set of network access controls based on experience
to date.</h2>
</li>
</ul>
